title: Grateful Dead Live at McArthur Court, U of Oregon on 1981-08-16
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > R8Brain > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 04/2016
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil-> El Paso-> Loser, Minglewood Blues, Peggy-O-> Little Red Rooster, Deal

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger, Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums*-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

*W Ken Kesey, Zane Kesey & Ken Babbs and The Thunder Machine

reviews.review_text:
go Eugene! great sounding tape here.   MacCourt was a horrible place to try to project clear sound, but this taper got a good pull somehow.

The scarlet > fire really has a groovy undercurrent, a version worth a listen!

Perfect show/tape This show is fantastic. There is simply very positive energy coming from the band and Jerry. It just feels like they are putting so much joy into it, compared to an East Coast show ( I’m from NY)…not that there were not good East coast shows this year….there are many…but this one just feels different to me…sometimes it just came together so well, and this is one of those.  A real gem!
